position : sr . devops engineer location : los angeles ca duration : 6 month steam mission : this team currently consists of passionate engineers who strive to demonstrate excellence in the field of devops . we are not only responsible for the up time of the various . com websites , but a large portion of the job is to innovate . historically , once infrastructure is configured and working it is mandated that there are no more changes to the system . not here . similar to netflix and chaos monkey , we frequently and deliberately rebuild our entire system in an automated fashion using tools such as jenkins , ansible , elastic search , and run deck . these activities help us not only discover pain points in our system but it gives us the opportunity to continually improve . how do we guarantee geographic redundancy ? how do we get code to production faster ? 15 minutes to rebuild a system , how can we get it down to 5 ? instead of mon go , should we use cassandra ? do we even need a database for this application ? how can we orchestrate a cloud fail over from one provider to another ? who are we looking for ? we want someone who has an insatiable thirst for technology , desire to learn and grow individually , with the team , and the business . what open_source technology is available that can be applied as part of our tool set ? how do we optimize performance , reduce downtime , and automate ? let s discuss this over our weekly team lunches / white board sessions . we want someone who is willing to challenge the status quo and make a difference . do you know_how to program in python , would you like to learn ? this is an extremely challenging position but would be the perfect fit for someone who wants to contribute and grow . let s get more involved in the community by attending meet ups and conferences . below is a list of technologies we currently use . we tend to be technology agnostic whatever is the best fit for the job . technologies we use : automation : ansible repositories : cvs , svn , git web architectures : lamp stack , java , nodejs scripting : bash , python cloud providers / cdn racks pace , aws , and akamai database : mysql , mon go central authentication : ldap architectures and configuration , radius , tacacs , ad encrypted authentication : rsa / pki keys , ssl , ipsec , etc . network operation tools : nagios , log stash , elastic search operating_systems : rhel .
